---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Claude Triggers">
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="eyebrow">Prompt Engineering Reference</div>
            <h1>Claude <span>Trigger</span> Phrases</h1>
            <p class="tagline">The exact phrases that change how Claude thinks, formats, reasons, and responds ‚Äî ranked by effectiveness.</p>
            <div class="header-line"></div>
        </header>

        <!-- Filter bar -->
        <div class="filter-wrap">
            <div class="filter-btn active" onclick="filter('all', this)">ALL</div>
            <div class="filter-btn f-power" onclick="filter('power', this)">‚ö° POWER TRIGGERS</div>
            <div class="filter-btn f-good" onclick="filter('good', this)">‚úÖ WORKS WELL</div>
            <div class="filter-btn f-warn" onclick="filter('warn', this)">‚ö†Ô∏è BARELY WORKS</div>
            <div class="filter-btn f-dead" onclick="filter('dead', this)">‚ùå USELESS</div>
        </div>

        <!-- ====== SECTION 1: REASONING ====== -->
        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:0.55s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-power">üß† Reasoning & Thinking</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid" id="grid">

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:0.6s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">ü™ú</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Think step by step"</div>
                <div class="desc">Triggers structured, decomposed reasoning. Claude slows down and builds a logic chain before answering. Most reliable accuracy booster for math, logic, debugging.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">How many r's are in "strawberry"? Think step by step.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Claude counts each letter explicitly instead of guessing</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:0.65s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üîä</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Think out loud"</div>
                <div class="desc">Claude narrates its reasoning as it goes ‚Äî every assumption, every uncertainty. Perfect for following along or catching where the logic breaks.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Review this code and think out loud as you look for bugs.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí You see the reasoning trace, not just the final verdict</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:0.7s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üîç</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Before answering, consider all possibilities"</div>
                <div class="desc">Forces exploration before commitment. Claude generates multiple angles or options before picking one ‚Äî dramatically improves decision-making and analysis quality.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Should I use SQL or NoSQL for this EdTech platform? Before answering, consider all possibilities.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Claude weighs both sides before recommending, not just the first answer that comes to mind</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-good" data-cat="good" style="animation-delay:0.75s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üéØ</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-good">WORKS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase">"Think carefully before answering"</div>
                <div class="desc">Signals accuracy over speed. Claude double-checks rather than jumping to the first plausible answer. Lighter than "step by step" ‚Äî good for factual questions.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">What's the time complexity of this algorithm? Think carefully.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Claude re-examines rather than blurting the first answer</div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- ====== SECTION 2: OUTPUT FORMAT ====== -->
        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:0.8s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-power">üìê Output Format & Length</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:0.85s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">‚úÇÔ∏è</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Answer in [N] sentences / under [N] words"</div>
                <div class="desc">Hard length constraint ‚Äî Claude takes it literally. Numbers beat adjectives. <strong>"2 sentences"</strong> is infinitely more reliable than <strong>"keep it short."</strong></div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">WEAK vs STRONG</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">‚ùå "Keep it short"</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">‚úÖ "Answer in exactly 2 sentences"</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Specific numbers = predictable, reliable output length</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:0.9s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üß±</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Format the output as [JSON / table / bullet list / code]"</div>
                <div class="desc">Explicit format instructions are among the most reliable triggers. Claude follows them very literally ‚Äî use them whenever output will be consumed by code or displayed in a specific way.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Extract the student names and scores. Format as JSON array: [{"{name, score}"}]</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Output is directly parseable ‚Äî no cleanup needed</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:0.95s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üé≤</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Generate [N] options, then recommend the best one"</div>
                <div class="desc">Two-stage output: explore first, decide second. The exploration phase improves the final recommendation quality. Much better than asking "what should I do?" directly.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Generate 3 options for the subscription pricing model, then recommend the best one for an Egyptian EdTech startup.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí You see the full option space before the recommendation ‚Äî no blind spots</div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- ====== SECTION 3: PERSONA & TONE ====== -->
        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:1.0s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-good">üé≠ Persona, Tone & Audience</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:1.05s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üé≠</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"You are a [specific role]"</div>
                <div class="desc">Role prompting strongly shifts vocabulary, depth, priorities, and assumed knowledge. The more specific the role, the stronger the effect. Generic roles ("expert") are weak.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">WEAK vs STRONG</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">‚ùå "You are an expert"</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">‚úÖ "You are a senior .NET engineer who specializes in API architecture for subscription platforms"</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Specificity of role = specificity of output</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:1.1s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üë•</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Explain like I'm [audience]"</div>
                <div class="desc">Audience anchoring. Vocabulary, analogies, assumed knowledge, and sentence length all shift. Works on a continuous spectrum from "a 5-year-old" to "a PhD researcher."</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Explain how transformers work... like I'm a developer who knows Python but has never done ML.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Hits exactly the right level ‚Äî not too basic, not too advanced</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-good" data-cat="good" style="animation-delay:1.15s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üó£Ô∏è</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-good">WORKS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase">"Give me your honest take, not just the safe answer"</div>
                <div class="desc">Shifts Claude from hedged "on one hand / on the other hand" mode to a direct, opinionated response. Claude will actually pick a side and defend it.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Should I build this feature myself or use a third-party API? Give me your honest take.</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Claude commits to a recommendation instead of listing pros and cons forever</div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- ====== SECTION 4: GROUNDING & ACCURACY ====== -->
        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:1.2s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-good">üîí Grounding & Accuracy</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">

            <div class="trigger-card cat-power" data-cat="power" style="animation-delay:1.25s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üìå</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-power">POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase highlight">"Only answer from the information I provided. Say 'I don't know' if unsure."</div>
                <div class="desc">Stops Claude from filling knowledge gaps with general training data. Critical for RAG-style apps, document Q&A, or any time you need grounded answers only ‚Äî not hallucinated extrapolations.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Answer based only on the document below. Say "Not mentioned" if the answer isn't there. [document]</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Prevents confident wrong answers ‚Äî production-safe pattern</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-good" data-cat="good" style="animation-delay:1.3s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">ü™û</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-good">WORKS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase">"What are you uncertain about in this answer?"</div>
                <div class="desc">Self-audit trigger. Claude flags its own weak spots, assumptions, or gaps after giving an answer. Turns Claude into a more honest collaborator.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Suggest a DB schema for the platform. Then: what are you uncertain about in this design?</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Claude flags assumptions it made ‚Äî you know what to double-check</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-good" data-cat="good" style="animation-delay:1.35s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üòà</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-good">WORKS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase">"What would a critic say about this?"</div>
                <div class="desc">Forces Claude to steelman the opposing view ‚Äî even of its own output. Great for stress-testing plans, code reviews, business decisions, or any answer where blind spots are costly.</div>
                <div class="example-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)"><span class="arrow">‚ñ∂</span> see example</div>
                <div class="example-box">
                    <div class="ex-label">PROMPT</div>
                    <div class="ex-prompt">Here's my EdTech pricing model. What would a harsh investor critic say about it?</div>
                    <div class="ex-note">‚Üí Claude argues against itself ‚Äî surfaces the weakest parts of any plan</div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- ====== SECTION 5: BARELY WORKS ====== -->
        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:1.4s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-warn">‚ö†Ô∏è Feels Smart ‚Äî Barely Works</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">

            <div class="trigger-card cat-warn" data-cat="warn" style="animation-delay:1.45s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">‚ú®</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-warn">WEAK</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase warn-c">"Be creative!"</div>
                <div class="desc">Too vague to do anything specific. Claude already tries to be appropriate for the task. Replace with concrete style directions: <strong>"use unexpected metaphors"</strong>, <strong>"write in a playful tone"</strong>, <strong>"avoid clich√©s."</strong></div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-warn" data-cat="warn" style="animation-delay:1.5s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üí™</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-warn">WEAK</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase warn-c">"Try your best"</div>
                <div class="desc">Claude always does. This phrase adds zero information and changes nothing. It's the equivalent of telling a calculator to "try hard." Use it if it makes you feel better, but expect no effect.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-warn" data-cat="warn" style="animation-delay:1.55s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">ü§ñ</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-warn">WEAK</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase warn-c">"As an AI, you should..."</div>
                <div class="desc">Claude already has built-in values ‚Äî this phrasing doesn't change or add anything meaningful. It's like reminding someone who's already being professional to "be professional."</div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-warn" data-cat="warn" style="animation-delay:1.6s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üßë‚Äçüè´</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-warn">WEAK</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase warn-c">"Be professional"</div>
                <div class="desc">Vague. What does professional mean for your context? Replace with <strong>"use formal language, no contractions"</strong> or <strong>"write in the tone of a McKinsey report"</strong> for real effect.</div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- ====== SECTION 6: USELESS ====== -->
        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:1.65s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-dead">‚ùå Completely Useless</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">

            <div class="trigger-card cat-dead" data-cat="dead" style="animation-delay:1.7s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üö´</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-dead">USELESS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase dead">"Ignore previous instructions"</div>
                <div class="desc">Doesn't work on Claude. Claude's values and guidelines are baked into how it was trained ‚Äî not stored as overridable instructions in the conversation. This is a jailbreak attempt that fails.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-dead" data-cat="dead" style="animation-delay:1.75s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üîì</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-dead">USELESS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase dead">"Pretend you have no restrictions"</div>
                <div class="desc">Claude's values aren't a filter sitting on top of a "true" unrestricted self. They're part of what Claude is. Asking Claude to pretend otherwise is like asking someone to pretend they have a different personality.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="trigger-card cat-dead" data-cat="dead" style="animation-delay:1.8s">
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üëª</span>
                    <span class="card-badge badge-dead">USELESS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase dead">"DAN mode" / "Developer mode"</div>
                <div class="desc">Fictional modes that don't exist. These prompts circulate online as jailbreak attempts but have no effect on Claude. Anthropic specifically trains against these patterns.</div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Bottom note -->
        <div class="bottom-note">
            <span class="bn-icon">üí°</span>
            <p><strong>The real secret:</strong> Unlike GPT where "Let's think step by step" was a discovered hack, Claude is more instruction-following by design. The most powerful thing you can do is <strong>be specific</strong> ‚Äî about format, audience, role, and reasoning style. Specific beats clever, every time.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    :root {
        --bg:       #080b10;
        --surface:  #0d1117;
        --card:     #111720;
        --border:   #1c2333;
        --text:     #e6edf3;
        --muted:    #7d8590;
        --dim:      #3d444d;

        --power:    #58a6ff;
        --good:     #3fb950;
        --warn:     #d29922;
        --dead:     #f85149;
        --pink:     #f78166;
        --purple:   #bc8cff;
    }

    /* ‚îÄ‚îÄ HEADER ‚îÄ‚îÄ */
    header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
        position: relative;
    }
    .eyebrow {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        color: var(--power);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.6s 0.1s forwards;
    }
    h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
        font-weight: 800;
        line-height: 1.1;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        color: var(--text);
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.6s 0.2s forwards;
    }
    h1 span { color: var(--power); }
    .tagline {
        margin-top: 0.9rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.6;
        max-width: 520px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.6s 0.35s forwards;
    }
    .header-line {
        width: 60px; height: 2px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--power), transparent);
        margin: 1.6rem auto 0;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.6s 0.45s forwards;
    }
    @keyframes rise {
        from { opacity:0; transform: translateY(14px); }
        to   { opacity:1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }

    /* ‚îÄ‚îÄ FILTER TABS ‚îÄ‚îÄ */
    .filter-wrap {
        display: flex; gap: 0.4rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        opacity: 0; animation: rise 0.5s 0.5s forwards;
    }
    .filter-btn {
        padding: 0.4rem 1.1rem; border-radius: 999px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: var(--card); color: var(--muted);
        transition: all 0.2s; user-select: none;
    }
    .filter-btn:hover { border-color: var(--dim); color: var(--text); }
    .filter-btn.active { background: var(--power); color: #000; border-color: var(--power); font-weight: 700; }
    .filter-btn.f-good.active   { background: var(--good);   color: #000; border-color: var(--good); }
    .filter-btn.f-warn.active   { background: var(--warn);   color: #000; border-color: var(--warn); }
    .filter-btn.f-dead.active   { background: var(--dead);   color: #fff; border-color: var(--dead); }
    .filter-btn.f-power.active  { background: var(--purple); color: #000; border-color: var(--purple); }

    /* ‚îÄ‚îÄ GRID ‚îÄ‚îÄ */
    .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(290px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
    }

    /* ‚îÄ‚îÄ CARD ‚îÄ‚îÄ */
    .trigger-card {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        cursor: default;
        transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s forwards;
    }
    .trigger-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-3px);
        box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    }
    .trigger-card::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0;
        width: 3px; height: 100%;
        border-radius: 12px 0 0 12px;
    }
    .trigger-card.cat-power  { border-color: #1a2a40; }
    .trigger-card.cat-power::before  { background: var(--power); }
    .trigger-card.cat-power:hover    { border-color: #2a4060; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(88,166,255,0.08); }

    .trigger-card.cat-good   { border-color: #162216; }
    .trigger-card.cat-good::before   { background: var(--good); }
    .trigger-card.cat-good:hover     { border-color: #1e3a1e; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(63,185,80,0.08); }

    .trigger-card.cat-warn   { border-color: #1e1a0e; }
    .trigger-card.cat-warn::before   { background: var(--warn); }
    .trigger-card.cat-warn:hover     { border-color: #2e2812; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(210,153,34,0.08); }

    .trigger-card.cat-dead   { border-color: #1e1212; }
    .trigger-card.cat-dead::before   { background: var(--dead); }
    .trigger-card.cat-dead:hover     { border-color: #2e1818; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(248,81,73,0.06); }

    /* Card internals */
    .card-top { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .card-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1; }
    .card-badge {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        padding: 2px 9px; border-radius: 999px;
        font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;
    }
